ANC veteran and businessman Tokyo Sexwale addresses the media in Midrand on money allegedly stolen from the WSB Heritage Fund. Sexwale said the money was meant to help poor students with free education and fight against the COVID-19 pandemic. He said he was one of the two people in charge of the fund, together with what he called a “very powerful family”. According to Sexwale, the money came through the Reserve Bank. The Reserve Bank has described Sexwale’s allegations as unfounded and says it’s a scam. Below is Sexwale’s address: 